===Noun===
{{en-noun|Christianities|-}}

# The belief that [[Jesus Christ]] (as he is called by [[Christian]]s) was "the son of God" (either in a metaphorical or literal sense) and was allowed to be consumed of and destroyed by [[sin]] (which is spoken of in this case as more of a [[disease]] or [[substance]] rather than a immoral action) in his crucifixion on the cross in order to act as payment for humanity's [[iniquity]] and [[vanity]] in a sort of alchemically philosophical and metaphorical sacrificed lamb.

